revision.text:
'''[[Capital punishment]]''' in '''[[Georgia (country)|Georgia]]''' was completely abolished on the May 1, 2000 when Protocol No. 6 to the [[ECHR]] was signed. Later Georgia also adopted the Second Optional Protocol to the [[ICCPR]]. The death penalty was replaced with [[life imprisonment]].

The last death sentence carried out in Georgia took place in 1997. It was carried out for murder; the prisoner was executed by a single shot to the back of the head.

