{{Infobox law enforcement agency | agencyname = Border Guard Command | nativename = فرماندهی مرزبانی | logo = [[File:Marzbani.svg|250px]] | country = Iran | national = yes | formedyear = 2000 | parent_agency = [[Law Enforcement Force of Islamic Republic of Iran]] | paramilitary = yes | gendarmerie = yes | speciality1 = border | speciality2 = coast | speciality3 = water | speciality4 = customs | chief1name = [[Brigadier general]] Qasem Rezaee }} '''Islamic Republic of Iran Border Guard Command''' ({{lang-fa|فرماندهی مرزبانی جمهوری اسلامی ایران}}), commonly known as '''NAJA Border Guard''' ({{lang-fa|مرزبانی ناجا}}), is a subdivision of [[Law Enforcement Force of Islamic Republic of Iran]] (NAJA) and [[Iran]]'s sole agency that performs [[border guard]] and [[border control|control]] in land borders, and [[coast guard]] in maritime borders. The unit was founded in 2000, and from 1991 to 2000, the unit's duties was done by of Security deputy of [[Law Enforcement Force of Islamic Republic of Iran|NAJA]]. Before 1991, border control was [[Persian Gendarmerie|Gendarmerie]]'s duty.<ref>{{cite|url=http://marzbani.police.ir/?fkeyid=&siteid=26&pageid=1998|title=کلیاتی از تاریخ مرزبانی جمهوری اسلامی ایران|publisher=Islamic Republic of Iran Border Guard Command|language=Persian|accessdate=1 April 2015}}</ref>
