'''Jacob Raphael Kaulla''' (died 1 May 1810, [[Hechingen]]) was a German court banker; born at [[Buchau]] on the [[Feder-See]] about the middle of the eighteenth century.
By a decree dated 27 June 1806, King [[Frederick of Württemberg]], "in view of the various services that the Kaulla family has rendered to the country in critical periods", conferred upon Jacob and a number of his immediate relatives and their descendants of both sexes all rights of citizenship in [[Württemberg]]. Jacob Kaulla and his sister [[Madame Kaulla]] were distinguished as [[philanthropist]]s.
